'''Folklorismus''' is a concept used in [[folkloristics]] and [[ethnology]]. It was developed by the German ethnologists Hans Moser and Hermann Bausinger, and bears similarities with the concepts of [[invented tradition]] and [[fakelore]].{{sfn|Radulovic|2017|p=69}}

The Serbian folklorist Nemanja Radulovic argued that [[Slavic Native Faith]] could be understood as a form of folklorismus.{{sfn|Radulovic|2017|p=69}}

