'''Stein Barth-Heyerdahl''' (12 July 1909<ref>{{cite book|title=Studenterne fra ...|date=1920|publisher=A. Cammermeyer|page=14|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1OQwAQAAMAAJ|accessdate=11 August 2017|language=no|quote=Gift i Kristiania 1897 med skogforvalter i Hedemarken Agnar johannes Barth, f. paa Lillehammer 26 august 1871, søn av forstmester jacob Bøckmann Barth, ... Født i Nesna prestegjeld i Nordland 29 juli 1876, søn av politimester Oscar Heyerdahl, Kragerø, og Karoline Fredrikke jenssen. ... Wiig, Sandnessjøen, og Henriette jacobsen. Barn: 1. Stein, f. 12 juli 1909, 2. Synøve, f. 30 december 1910, 3. Gerd, f.}}</ref> – 1972) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] art painter and [[Nazism|national socialist]].<ref name="Sørensen">{{ Cite book | author = [[Øystein Sørensen|Sørensen, Øystein]] | year = 1989 | title = Hitler eller Quisling?: ideologiske brytninger i Nasjonal samling 1940-1945 | isbn = 8202119928 | publisher = Cappelen | url = http://urn.nb.no/URN:NBN:no-nb_digibok_2012121108054 | pages = 76–78 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> A reluctant member of [[Nasjonal Samling]] (NS) briefly after its founding in 1933–34 and from 1941, he was mostly active in the [[National Socialist Workers' Party of Norway]] (NNSAP) during the 1930s.<ref name="Sørensen"/> He was editor of the short-lived NNSAP-paper ''Nasjonalsocialisten'' in 1934–35.<ref>{{ Cite book| author = Jensen, Tom B. | year = 1992 | title = Nasjonal samlings periodiske skrifter 1933-1945: en bibliografi | isbn = 8276950000 | publisher = Grafisk Media | url = http://urn.nb.no/URN:NBN:no-nb_digibok_2008062501028 | pages = 60–61 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> Barth-Heyerdahl lived in [[Berlin]] for extended periods during [[World War II]], and became part of the circle around the NS-critical periodical ''[[Ragnarok (periodical)|Ragnarok]]'', which espoused [[Pan-Germanism|pan-German]] and [[Heathenry (new religious movement)|neopagan]] ideologies.<ref name="Sørensen"/> Along with [[Per Imerslund]], he was one of Norway's strongest proponents of racialist pagan ideas.<ref>{{Cite book|author=[[Terje Emberland|Emberland, Terje]]|title=Religion og rase: nyhedenskap og nazisme i Norge 1933-1945|url=https://books.google.no/books?id=nzsTAQAAMAAJ&q=%22Stein+Barth-Heyerdahl%22&dq=%22Stein+Barth-Heyerdahl%22&hl=no&sa=X&redir_esc=y|year=2003|publisher=Humanist forlag|isbn= 9788290425536 |language=Norwegian|page=139}}</ref>
